Full Description: A picturesque campus in one of Southern California’s most pleasant small cities, Pasadena City College (PCC) offers professional programs as well as strong academics for students who wish to transfer to a four-year school. Right next door is the city of Pasadena which has world-class shopping, great restaurants, theatres and museums. Academics at PCC include a Teacher Education program and programs in Business, Engineering, English, Health Sciences, Languages, Mathematics, Library Science and Performing and Visual Arts. Many students from these programs transfer to UC, Cal State, or private universities and colleges. PCC also has a substantial number of professional two-year programs in such fields as Accounting, Automotive Technology, Cosmetology, Dental Hygiene, Nursing, Paralegal Studies and Speech Language Pathology Assisting. There is also a professional program in Film and Television Production. The PCC campus sponsors a student-run radio station, a student art gallery, a theatre, as well as student organizations and recreational opportunities. PCC has an open admissions policy for all students, regardless of educational background. Those who reside in California can enjoy a reduced tuition. Financial aid is also available to those who qualify. There is also an Upward Bound program for students from challenged home environments.

Description: Howlyr allows users to add pop culture audio soundbites to social media photos & text message conversations through an iMessage extension.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: At a loss for words?  There's a Howl for that. Search, create and share pop culture soundbites (“Howls”) to create the soundtrack of your life in iMessage and on social media. Howlyr is a mobile application which allows users to share authentic pop culture soundbites via text message through the Howlyr iMessage extension, and to attach those soundbites to personal photos to share to their other social media platforms (e.g., Instagram, Facebook).   Text-based communication has rapidly changed since the introduction of smartphones.  While texting used to be just that – i.e., text only – one could not imagine communicating without Emojis, Bitmojis and gifs, all of which have become languages in and of themselves.  As the voice becomes increasingly integrated into communication through smartphone digital voice assistants like Siri, smart speakers like Amazon’s Alexa, and even Apple’s Animoji, Howlyr further integrates the intersection between technology and the voice into everyday text message conversations and social media posts, creating a new ability to convey tone and articulate ideas that words alone (and even images) cannot.

Description: Novodiax is a biotech startup dedicated to advancing cancer and autoimmunity diagnostics through innovative rapid immunoassays.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Novodiax is a biotech startup dedicated to advancing cancer and autoimmunity diagnostics through innovative rapid immunoassays. Our revolutionary ihcDirect® assays are listed for in vitro diagnostic (IVD) use and provide immunohistochemistry (IHC) results in as little as 10 minutes on frozen tissues! They also provide workflow benefits for formalin-fixed, paraffin-embedded (FFPE) tissues, helping reduce assay time by up to 40-60 minutes. ihcDirect works by directly conjugating primary antibodies to our proprietary and sensitive polymerized horseradish peroxidase (polyHRP) detection system, thus delivering immunoassays for histology and cytology (2020) that: - Are lightning fast (~10 minutes) - Require minimal lab space and no specialized equipment - Can be performed at room temperature - Are simple to perform like H&E tests, yet provide the sensitivity and specificity of immunoassays Our assays are also perfect for helping you advance your research (see our ihcPrime™ and Q-Stain® products and custom services), develop cutting edge companion diagnostics (CDx), and more. Let’s partner together to make that happen! Visit our website or contact us to learn more. www.novodiax.com sales@novodiax.com
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

Description: LocalBonus allows consumers to earn cashback rewards from local merchants using their existing credit and debit cards.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: About Us LocalBonus allows consumers to use their existing credit & debit cards to automatically earn cash back rewards at local businesses. Consumers connect their existing cards to LocalBonus once, and automatically earn points towards cash back rewards with every purchase at over 1,000 different merchants. Participating merchants get an easy way to attract and retain customers without having to offer deals or discounts, no POS integration, and no employee training. They are headquartered in New York City, with merchants in Denver, New York City, Portland, Sacramento, and Seattle. For more information on LocalBonus, contact info@localbonus.com or visit www.LocalBonus.com. How It Works: Sign up on the LocalBonus site and connect your existing credit or debit cards to your account and start shopping at LocalBonus merchants. Points earned from shopping are automatically added to your account whenever you spend money at a LocalBonus merchant. LocalBonus is free to use. Rewards start at 4,000 points ($10 LocalBonus Cash) but the more you save, the more valuable your points become. Members can also earn bonus points through Facebook and Twitter promotions, as well as through the LocalBonus WolfPack. If 5 or more LocalBonus members shop at a merchant on any given day, members will earn double points at that merchant. As of April 2012: 5 cities - NYC, Denver, Portland, Sacramento, Seattle 1,000+ merchants

Description: NorthShore Bio (NSB) is developing a silicon-chip Molecular Detection Platform.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: NorthShore Bio (NSB) is developing a silicon-chip Molecular Detection Platform based on a proprietary, hybrid nanopore technology that combines solid-state, tunable nanopores with direct single molecule detection and integrated digital output. The initial focus is on direct RNA sequencing, and "next" generation DNA sequencing with major advances in read length, resolution, data analytics, and speed. NSB's new generation of molecular detection platform draws on methods harnessed from the silicon microchip industry. As the technology advances, it is expected to enable sequencing read lengths of >50,000bp, enabling sequencing of a whole human genome in less than 5 hours and at a cost of less than $500. NSB's chip platform also scales nicely into diagnostics applications, potentially enabling multiplexed assays at a fraction of their current cost. While still in development, NSB has successfully conquered several key hurdles on the way to a Proof of Concept, including demonstrating label-free single molecule detection (of DNA base transits).
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

These people are your inner circle – and while knowing them is crucial no matter your size, it is especially critical to startups working with limited resources. You may ask – why Labs? They purposely avoided “PR,” “marketing,” “communications” because they see too many issues in both market understanding and business execution across those areas. The idea of a lab spoke to us – a place where knowledge and understanding is brought to the table all while experimentation and a desire to discover “what’s next” keeps the wheels spinning. Description: Road Triage is a comprehensive, objective roadway assessment system that uses AI to provide quarterly pavement and lane line condition data.
Headquarters Regions: Research Triangle, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Road Triage is a comprehensive, objective roadway assessment system that provides regular updates on pavement and lane line conditions. Users receive more complete and consistent data than current manually collected road assessment methods at a lower cost. It is also significantly less expense than LIDAR-based approaches. Using fleet-sourced data collection from windshield mounted devices, Road Triage delivers results that are current, comprehensive, and consistent – without the drawbacks of human subjectivity. Workers avoid hazardous situations while collecting data. In addition to improving the allocation of maintenance resources, the resulting data supports root cause analysis, and predictive asset decay studies. Data Rich:  Road Triage provides actionable data with road segment scores for lane lines and pavement distress such as potholes, patches, multiple crack types, and pavement edge issues. These are color-coded, assessed/scored, and geo-tagged. Ride quality is also analyzed identifying bumps, dips/lifts, and roughness. Images are provided for identified issues. This level of detail provides a better understanding of road conditions without having to visit in person. Online management reports include quantified data visualization, maps, and exportable datasets for use in popular spreadsheet and GIS software.  High Quality:  The value of data depends on its quality. Road Triage’s AI algorithms consistently and accurately identify and assess pavement distress issues and lane lines. When compared to manual data collection and assessment methodology, Road Triage removes human subjectivity - resulting in more consistent and accurate results. Furthermore, the AI models are regularly updated and retrained. A team of specialists combs through new data enabling the AI models to learn from new experiences.  Reduced Costs and Safety:  High-quality road data at a low price is the cornerstone of Road Triage. The current process requires expensive LIDAR equipment and/or dedicated field staff to drive and walk the roads. This approach is dangerous for the workers walking unprotected on active roadways. Using Road Triage, road data are collected while fleets drive their typical routes, with no additional effort required for most roads. For roads not covered by typical fleet operations, data can be collected by simply driving them. There is no need to exit the vehicle and manually evaluate the roads. The reduced data collection and processing effort translates into a lower cost with increased data quality and frequency. Additionally, reconstructing roads costs approximately four times more than resurfacing them. Road Triage can provide asset conditions of the entire road network supporting early intervention thus reducing long-term costs and improving roadway safety.  USDOT Road to Zero:  Road Triage supports the vision and goals of the USDOT Road to Zero initiative – a collaborative effort among the NHTSA, FHWA, FMCSA, NSC, and state DOTs with the goal of ending fatalities on the nation’s roads. According to the USDOT, the lack of adequate roadway safety features and poor roadway condition are likely a significant contributing factor to motor vehicle accidents. The timely identification and assessment of poor roadway markings and pavement distress from Road Triage can be instrumental to keeping roadways in optimal operational condition.  Robocist works with state and local transportation organizations, adding value to their transportation networks by providing quantifiable access to current, relevant roadway data, asset conditions, and the associated trends that support efficient asset management.
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Government and Military, Information Technology, Internet Services, Navigation and Mapping, Other, Software, Transportation
